text.tspan: The smuggler picked up my
child and threw him into the
water so everyone would jump
in.
We have been here for 12 hours and have had
no food, no water. My children are cold, my
baby is sick. I would rather die in Syria with my
family than here in this horrible place.
Every day an average of 42 500
people have to leave their homes
dure to war, conflict or human
rights violations. In total there are
60 mullion refugees worldwide.
It was horrible the last three days...
There are no rooms, no hotels, no
bathrooms, no beds, no anything.
51% of the worlds refugees
are under 18 years old.
My mother cried a lot when I decided I had
to leave but I had to. If my family would get
killed or hurt because of my activities, I
would live the rest of my days in shame.
In 2015, 3620 people
have died trying to
get to Europe.
